lass=\"para\">Protecting the Earth from the threat of asteroid impacts means first knowing where they are. NASA &amp; Planetary Resources are harnessing the incredible potential of innovators, makers and citizen scientists by opening up the search. In an increasingly connected world, NASA recognizes the value of the public as a partner in addressing some of the country’s most pressing challenges. We need your help in identifying asteroids - and to help further this effort, we’ve built an application that enables everyone, everywhere, to help solve this global challenge.\n<a class=\"btnwatchTV\" style=\"margin-top: 10px; margin-left: 290px;\" onclick=\"popupYT(\'7wUrXAvWDOE\',\'NASA\'s Asteroid Data Hunter\');\" href=\"javascript:;\"> </a></div>'),(162,29,'Banner Image','372'),(163,29,'Video YouTube ID','7wUrXAvWDOE'),(164,29,'open_graph_title','NASA&#039;s Asteroid Data Hunter Challenge'),(165,29,'open_graph_description','Calling all coders interested in science and protecting planet Earth! We need YOUR help to locate near-earth asteroids by creating an advanced algorithm that sifts through imaging data. Compete for your chance at $35,000 in prize money and bragging rights as a protector of our planet'),(166,29,'open_graph_type','article'),(167,29,'open_graph_image','http://www.topcoder.com/asteroids/files/2014/07/Asteroid_Data_Hunter_V2.1-e1404385533572.jpg'),(168,29,'twitter_cards_post_description','Calling all coders interested in science and protecting planet Earth! We need YOUR help to locate near-earth asteroids by creating an advanced algorithm that sifts through imaging data'),(169,29,'twitter_cards_post_title','NASA\'s Asteroid Data Hunter Challenge'),(170,29,'twitter_cards_post_creator_username','@topcoder'),(171,29,'twitter_cards_post_type','summary'),(172,29,'twitter_cards_post_image','http://www.topcoder.com/asteroids/files/2014/07/Asteroid_Data_Hunter_twitter_card.jpg'),(173,29,'twitter_cards_post_iframe',''),(174,29,'twitter_cards_post_stream',''),(175,34,'_wp_page_template','challengeDetails.php'),(176,34,'_edit_last','3'),(177,34,'Challenge Banner Text','<h2>NASA’s Disruption Tolerant Networking Challenge Series</h2>\nWelcome to the NASA Disruption Tolerant Networking (DTN) project. DTN is an approach to computer network architecture that seeks to address the technical issues in heterogeneous networks that may lack continuous network connectivity.\n\nExamples of such networks are those operating in mobile or extreme terrestrial environments, or planned networks in space. Disruption may occur because of the limits of wireless radio range, sparsity of mobile nodes, energy resources, attack, and noise.'),(178,111,'_edit_last','3'),(179,111,'_wp_page_template','singlecolumn.php'),(180,111,'Challenge Banner Text','<h2>About the Asteroid Grand Challenge Series</h2>\n<div class=\"para\">Welcome to the Asteroid Grand Challenge Series sponsored by the NASA Tournament Lab. The Asteroid Grand Challenge Series is comprised of a number of topcoder Challenges that aim to get the world involved in finding asteroid threats to human populations.</div>'),(181,111,'the_content','Welcome to the Asteroid Grand Challenge Series sponsored by the NASA Tournament Lab. The Asteroid Grand Challenge Series is comprised of a number of topcoder Challenges that aim to get the world involved in finding asteroid threats to human populations.'),(182,111,'Banner Image','380'),(183,351,'Banner Image','384'),(184,351,'_edit_last','3'),(185,351,'_wp_page_template','challengeDetails.php'),(186,351,'Challenge Banner Text','<h2><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\">Asteroid Tracker </span></h2>\n<div class=\"para\">\n\nThe Asteroid Tracker challenge tasks competitors to develop optimization algorithms for Near Earth Object tracking using monolithic radar arrays. The winning solutions must first efficiently determine the necessary subarray allocation required to track all objects given a particular data set, then eventually determine the optimal configuration of the array, as well as how this optimal configuration will change if additional dishes are added.\n<a style=\"color: #ff0000;\" href=\"https://github.com/nasa/NTL-Asteroid-Tracker\">Asteroid Tracker (KaBOOM) Github repository </a>\n<a class=\"btnwatchTV AsteroidTracker\" style=\"margin-top: 10px; margin-left: 290px;\" onclick=\"popupYT(\'72bKusFX0Tg\',\'NASA\'s Asteroid Tracker\');\" href=\"javascript:;\"> </a>\n\n</div>'),(187,351,'Video YouTube ID','72bKusFX0Tg'),(188,351,'open_graph_image',''),(189,351,'twitter_cards_post_description',''),(190,351,'twitter_cards_post_title',''),(191,351,'open_graph_title',''),(192,351,'open_graph_description',''),(193,351,'open_graph_type','blog'),(194,351,'twitter_cards_post_creator_username',''),(195,351,'twitter_cards_post_type','summary'),(196,351,'twitter_cards_post_image',''),(197,351,'twitter_cards_post_iframe',''),(198,351,'twitter_cards_post_stream',''),(199,355,'_edit_last','3'),(200,355,'Challenge Banner Text','<h2>Asteroid Data Hunter – LAUNCHING 03/17/14!</h2>\n<div id=\"stcpDiv\">The Asteroid Data Hunter challenge tasks competitors to develop significantly improved algorithms to identify asteroids in images from ground-based telescopes. The winning solution must increase the detection sensitivity, minimize the number of false positives, ignore imperfections in the data, and run effectively on all computers.\n<a class=\"btnwatchTV\" onclick=\"popupYT(\'gJtbLhRHgog\',\'Modal Window title goes here\');\" href=\"javascript:;\">Asteroid Hunters! <span class=\"nl\">Watch this video for an overview of the challenge &amp; learn how to get involved!</span></a></div>'),(201,355,'_wp_page_template','challengeDetails.php'),(202,355,'Banner Image','358'),(203,396,'_menu_item_type','post_type'),(204,396,'_menu_item_menu_item_parent','0'),(205,396,'_menu_item_object_id','29'),(206,396,'_menu_item_object','page'),(207,396,'_menu_item_target',''),(208,396,'_menu_item_classes','a:1:{i:0;s:0:\"\";}'),(209,396,'_menu_item_xfn','')